    "author_association": "NONE",
    "body": "### Problem\n\n**Description:**\nIn Neovim 0.12, when using command-line mode (`:`), pressing `<Tab>` to cycle through completion items skips entries - it jumps two items instead of one.\n\nhttps://github.com/user-attachments/assets/3774bd77-4f95-4244-83de-f6cc5a536aa3\n\n### Steps to reproduce\n\n**Steps to reproduce**\n\n1. Start Neovim with a clean environment:\n\n   ```\n   nvim --clean\n   ```\n\n2. Enter command-line mode:\n\n   ```\n   :\n   ```\n\n3. Type a partial command, for example:\n\n   ```\n   tab\n   ```\n\n4. Press `<Tab>` repeatedly to cycle through completion items\n\n5. Observe the order in which completion candidates are selected\n\n**Observed behavior:**\nEach `<Tab>` press skips entries (cycles through items two at a time instead of one).\n\n### Expected behavior\n\nPressing `<Tab>` in command-line mode should cycle through completion items sequentially, moving to the next item one-by-one without skipping any entries.\n\n\n### Nvim version (nvim -v)\n\n0.12\n\n### Vim (not Nvim) behaves the same?\n\nno, vim 9.1.697\n\n### Operating system/version\n\nUbuntu 24.04.4 LTS (Noble Numbat) x86_64\n\n### Terminal name/version\n\nAlacritty 0.13.2\n\n### $TERM environment variable\n\nxterm-256color\n\n### Installation\n\ncurl -LO https://github.com/neovim/ncurl -LO https://github.com/neovim/neovim/releases/latest/download/nvim-linux-x86_64.tar.gzeovim/releases/latest/download/nvim-linux-x86_64.tar.gz",
